INSERT INTO `idx_idx_fotjc_5452` VALUES ('On the last mission as we were crossing a river to get back I was filled with joy at the thought of all the people who have made it possible for this work to go on. I wanted to see and thank each of you. We do hope we can and know that finally in heaven we will.','Flight of the Jungle Chicken April 2005','/IDX/FotJC/2005/20050715_FJC.html','','2005-07-15','','CCB','','1','','SELF','','',''),('We spent most of the past year in the areas under attack by the Burma Army. Over 25,000 people are newly displaced and attacks continue. Thanks to your help, we now have 29 fulltime relief teams bringing emergency help and love to people in the war zones of Burma. They shine a light on the actions of the dictators’ army and help to build up ethnic leaders united to serve their people. Thanks for being with us in this.','Flight of the Jungle Chicken','/IDX/FotJC/2007/20070401.html','','2007-04-01','','CCB','','1','','SELF','','',''),('We are now traveling in the USA and Europe to say thanks, see as many of you as we can and report on the situation in Burma.','Thank You from CCB','/IDX/FotJC/2007/20070620.html','','2007-06-20','','CCB','','1','','SELF','','',''),('We are now traveling back in the US after finishing a conference on Burma in Norway.','FLIGHT OF THE JUNGLE CHICKEN','/IDX/FotJC/2007/20070730.html','','2007-07-30','','CCB','','1','','SELF','','',''),('We are back in Thailand and getting ready to go into the field for continuing missions. We were overwhelmed by the love you all gave us and the support - spiritual, moral, and material.','FLIGHT OF THE JUNGLE CHICKEN','/IDX/FotJC/2007/20070910.html','','2007-09-10','','CCB','','1','','SELF','','',''),('I am sending this letter of thanks from the Karen State where we are training 18 new Karen, Karenni and Kachin humanitarian relief teams.','Thank You from the FBR Training Camp','/IDX/FotJC/2007/20071120.html','','2007-11-20','','FBR','','1','','SELF','','',''),('This letter was written by Karen and we are relaying it out from the Karen State where we just graduated 18 new FBR relief teams. We are now on relief missions with them. Thank you and may God bless you all this Christmas season. Love, your team here.','Karen\'s Christmas Story','/IDX/FotJC/2007/20071210.html','','2007-12-10','','CCB','','1','','','','',''),('Frontier Mission Project of the Presbyterian Church (USA)','Wa Outreach in Thailand,  Annual Report 2007','/IDX/FotJC/2008/20080330_wa.html','','2008-03-30','','CCB','','1','','','','','');
