INSERT INTO `idx_idx_prayer_day_of_prayer_2006_4241` VALUES ('','','','','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images','International Day of Prayer for Burma, 2006','DOP 2006 Images','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images','','',''),('','2005-12-16','','CCB','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/aung aung.jpg','Aung Aung: baby Karen boy who survived birth at 1.8 kilos. Read his story <a href=\"/IDX/News/20060108_aung_aung.html\">here</a>.','Aung Aung','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/aung aung.jpg','','',''),('','','','CCB','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/aung san suu kyi.jpg','Aung San Suu Kyi, a Nobel Peace Prize Laureate, celebrated her\r\n60th birthday during 2005. She has now spent over 10 years under\r\nhouse arrest and her detention was extended for at least 6 months\r\nin late November 2005. She is the leader of the National League for\r\nDemocracy, the party which won over 80% of the vote in the 1990\r\nelections in Burma.','Aung San Suu Kyi','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/aung san suu kyi.jpg','','',''),('','','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/bulldozer.jpg','The military dictatorship in Burma, the State Peace and Development Council (SPDC), moved their headquarters\r\nnorth to the city of Pyinmana during late 2005.','Bulldozer used by Burma Army in road building operations, 2005.','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/bulldozer.jpg','','',''),('','','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/burma army patrol.jpg','The military dictatorship in Burma, the State Peace and Development Council (SPDC), moved their headquarters\r\nnorth to the city of Pyinmana during late 2005.','Burma Army patrol, 2005.','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/burma army patrol.jpg','','',''),('','','','CCB','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/burma map.jpg','Burma is a country made up of many ethnic nationalities including the majority Burmans and the Karen, Shan, Karenni, Kachin, Arakan, Chin, Wa, Lahu and others.','Burma Map','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/burma map.jpg','','',''),('','','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/burma soldier.jpg','Burma Army soldier threatens villagers. This photo was taken at great risk by a\r\nrelief team, 2005.','Burma Army soldier','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/burma soldier.jpg','','',''),('','','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/destroyed home.jpg','Home destroyed by the Burma Army during attacks from\r\nSeptember to November 2005.','Destroyed Home','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/destroyed home.jpg','','',''),('','','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/destroyed rice carriers.jpg','The Burma Army systematically destroys villagers’ means of food production and storage as shown in picture above. Winnowing baskets and storage tins have been stabbed with knives or bayonets by the attacking Burma Army in Nyaunglebin District, western Karen State.','destroyed rice carriers','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/destroyed rice carriers.jpg','','',''),('','','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/fbr medic and patient.jpg','','Relief team medic and patient','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/fbr medic and patient.jpg','','',''),('','','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/forced labor 01.jpg','The Burma Army continues to force villagers in many\r\nareas of Burma to work for them on road projects, carrying\r\nsupplies, and building Burma Army camps, among other\r\nthings. The continual build-up of forces by the Burma Army\r\nand the infrastructure to support those forces is a burden\r\non the villagers. The forced labor is a violation of their basic\r\nhuman rights.','forced labor','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/forced labor 01.jpg','','',''),('','','','CCB','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/GLC 01.jpg','Thank you for praying for the children of Burma! The\r\nGood Life Club is a program based on the words of\r\nJesus in John 10:10, “The thief comes to kill and destroy,\r\nbut I have come that they may have life and have it\r\nabundantly!” The word abundant is so big and full…\r\nonly Jesus can truly meet their needs–any of our needs–\r\nin an abundant way. But in whatever way we are able, we\r\nhope to bring love and faith, along with tools for a good\r\nlife, body and soul. These include teaching, primarily\r\nbible lessons and healthcare, songs and games, and a\r\nschool pack for the teachers.','Good Life club','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/GLC 01.jpg','','',''),('','2005-12-16','','CCB','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/GLC 02.jpg','“The thief comes only\r\nto steal and kill and\r\ndestroy; I have come that\r\nthey may have life, and\r\nhave it to the full. I am\r\nthe good shepherd. The\r\ngood shepherd lays down\r\nhis life for the sheep.”\r\nJohn 10:10-11','Good Life Club','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/GLC 02.jpg','','',''),('','','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/Karenni medic.jpg','Karenni medic team provides IDPs with dental care, western Karen State,\r\nApril 2005.','Karenni medic','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/Karenni medic.jpg','','',''),('','','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/lahu medic.jpg','Lahu Relief team provides dental\r\ntreatment, Feb-May 2005. Shan State, Eastern Burma','Lahu medic','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/lahu medic.jpg','','',''),('','','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/land mines.jpg','The Burma Army and its allies use landmines to terrorize villagers.\r\nVillagers are forced to be human minesweepers and clean roads where the\r\nBurma Army has planted landmines.','land mines','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/land mines.jpg','','',''),('','','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/medic hsa kae.jpg','Medic Hsa Kae at relief team traiing, Nover 2005 <a href=/IDX/Features/medic_hsa_kae.html>story</a>','medic Hsa Kae','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/medic hsa kae.jpg','','',''),('','','','CCB','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/mules 01.jpg','One of 22 mules being used in the relief work inside Burma. Thank You to all who have helped in getting these mules for transport of emergency medicine and other supplies to the IDPs of Burma.','mule used for relief team work with son of a Karen leader','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/mules 01.jpg','','',''),('','','','CCB','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/mules 02.jpg','Responding to the needs of IDPs: In a place where\r\neverything has to be carried on your back, we are\r\ngrateful for all of you who support the new mule\r\nprogram for transporting medical and other relief\r\nsupplies. This is one of the many good things that\r\npeople are doing to help each other.','mule carrying supplies for relief team','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/mules 02.jpg','','',''),('','','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/relief team nurses.jpg','Relief team nurses on relief mission to IDPs in Toungoo\r\nDistrict, northwestern Karen State, January 2005. <br>\r\n<i>“Be joyful always; pray continually; give thanks in all\r\ncircumstances, for this is God’s will for you in Christ Jesus.”</i><br>\r\n1 Thessalonians 5:16-18','relief team nurses','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/relief team nurses.jpg','','',''),('','','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/saw ker paw.jpg','Saw Ker Paw, 24 years old, receives\r\ntreatment at a clinic after stepping\r\non a Burma Army landmine, western\r\nKaren State, 31 August 2005','Saw Ker Paw','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/saw ker paw.jpg','','',''),('','','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/shan FBR 01.jpg','The situation in Southern Shan State has deteriorated, with a total of 20,000 people\r\ndisplaced in the Mong Pan area. In this area the Burma Army continues its brutal\r\nsuppression of the Shan and other ethnic peoples.','Shan FBR team giving Good Life Club gifts to children','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/shan FBR 01.jpg','','',''),('','','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/shan FBR 02.jpg','A relief team documented the rape of an 8-year-old girl and a 13-year-old girl\r\nby Burma Army troops. They also reported attacks against civilians including;\r\nmurder, torture, forced labor, forced relocation, destruction of villages and land\r\nconfiscation. All of these human rights violations are ongoing. The team was able\r\nto provide medical care for over 2,000 people in hiding.','Shan relief team treating IDPs. Mar-May 2005.','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/shan FBR 02.jpg','','',''),('','','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/thee bo.jpg','Thee Bo, victim of a Burma Army\r\nlandmine, received treatment from a\r\nrelief team, Karenni State,\r\n15 January 2005','Thee Bo','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/thee bo.jpg','','',''),('','2005-08-01','','CCB','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/thu zar aung.jpg','Thu Zar Aung: 29-year-old Karen woman who was 32 weeks pregnant\r\nand dying from HIV/AIDS at the time of this picture. Zar Aung died after giving birth to son Aung Aung, who survived. Read a special CCB report <a href=\"/IDX/News/20060108_aung_aung.html\">here</a>. ','Thu Zar Aung','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/thu zar aung.jpg','','',''),('','2005-01-15','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/toungoo IDPs.jpg','Ways to take action for Burma: • Pray for Burma\r\n• Go see the situation with your own eyes\r\n• Encourage your government to take positive action for Burma\r\n• Help provide relief for IDPs such as educational supplies, medical\r\nsupplies, and mother, children and baby packs.','IDPs in Toungoo District, northwestern Karen State','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/toungoo IDPs.jpg','','',''),('','','','CCB','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/wa christians.jpg','Please pray for Burma:\r\nWhen asked what their country needed prayer for, young ethnic leaders\r\nat a relief team training in November 2005 responded with many prayer\r\nrequests, including prayer for the following:\r\n• That God’s love would light fires of faith and service all over Burma\r\n• Freedom and peace in Burma\r\n• The dictators and their army to start caring for their country and people\r\n• Political and other prisoners wrongly jailed to be freed\r\n• Unity among and between all ethnic groups and people in Burma','Wa Christian celebration, 2005','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/wa christians.jpg','','',''),('','','','FBR','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/women weavers.jpg','<b>Survival Strategies and Resistance by the IDPs</b><br>\r\nIn every area under Burma Army oppression, the IDPs and villagers do\r\nan amazing job of surviving and resisting attempts of complete control.\r\nThe people work together to escape the Burma Army and care for each\r\nother, sharing food and shelter. They try to continue the schooling\r\nof their children using rocks and blackboards and the jungle as a\r\nclassroom. They are not passive victims but return to their land as soon\r\nas the attacking troops depart. They refuse to give up. They restart their\r\nschools, rebuild their homes and do so with smiles and laughter; it is\r\ntruly amazing to witness. They demonstrate that force cannot crush the\r\nhuman spirit.','Women inside Karen State weave blankets for Karen and Karenni IDPs, February 2005','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/Images/women weavers.jpg','','',''),('','2006-03-12','','CCB','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/index.php','Global Day of Prayer For Burma 2006','Global Day of Prayer For Burma 2006','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/index.php','','',''),('','2006-03-12','pdf','CCB','','1','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/PFB2006.pdf','Day of Prayer 2006, brochure. (PDF) (En)','brochure -- Global Day of Prayer for Burma 2006 (pdf)','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2006/PFB2006.pdf','','','');
