INSERT INTO `idx_idx_prayer_day_of_prayer_2007_images_4598` VALUES ('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-01_1.jpg','<b>2006 Offensive by Burma Army Displaces Over 25,000 Villagers in Northern Karen State</b><br>\r\nThe people in these photos are some of the over 25,000 displaced by the Burma Army in the worst offensive since 1997. The unrelenting attacks in the Karen State are part of the plan by the dictators to completely dominate, chase out or crush any Karen people in these areas.','IDPs in the rain, Northern Karen State','','','','','',''),('','2006-12-27','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-02_1.jpg','<b>Population of Burma:</b>\r\nApproximately 50 million<br>\r\n<b>IDPs in Burma:</b>\r\nOver 1 million<br>\r\n<b>Refugees from Burma:</b>\r\nOver 1 million in countries\r\nneighboring Burma\r\nwith over 150,000 living\r\nin camps','Burma map','FBR','','','','',''),('','2006-12-27','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-02_2.jpg','Children from a Wa hostel performing a traditional dance.','Wa perform traditional dance.','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-03_1.jpg','Child in hiding in Mon Township, Karen State, following Burma Army attacks.','Child crying in Mon Township','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-03_2.jpg','Karen families flee Toungoo District.','Families fleeing Toungoo District.','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-03_3.jpg','Fleeing Burma Army’s attacking troops.','Fleeing Burma Army’s attacking troops.','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-03_4.jpg','<b>The Attackers</b><br>Burma Army soldiers in a Karen village. This photo was taken at great risk by a relief team leader hiding in an area occupied by the Burma Army.','Burma Army soldiers in a Karen village','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-04_1.jpg','Naw Eh Ywa Paw shown here recovering in late April at a new hiding\r\nplace. In November 2006 she had to flee again and is now in hiding with over 1,500 others.','Naw Eh Ywa Paw in recovery.','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-04_2.jpg','The remains of Naw Eh Ywa Paw\'s father, Saw Maw Keh, where he\r\nwas shot carrying her 80-year-old grandmother\r\n(who was also shot) as all three were trying to flee\r\nthe Burma Army.','Remains of Saw Maw Keh','','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-04_3.jpg','Relief team holds service for Naw Eh Ywa Paw’s father\r\nand grandmother with her aunt, the sister of\r\nSaw Maw Keh.\r\n','Service for Naw Eh Ywa Paw\'s father and grandmother','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-04_4.jpg','Eh Ywa Paw being\r\ntreated by an FBR team\r\nafter she was shot by\r\nBurma Army troops, early April 2006.','Eh Ywa Paw being treated for gunshot wounds.','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-05_1.jpg','Newborn Saw Brave, born in hiding during the 2006 offensive in northern Karen State.','Mother and newborn in Karen state','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-05_2.jpg','Karenni IDPs join in the 2006 Global Day of Prayer.','Karenni IDPs join in the 2006 Global Day of Prayer','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-06_1.jpg','Arakan relief team gives medical attention to displaced persons.','Arkakan relief team member','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-06_2.jpg','Burma Army attacks and chases Karenni villagers from their homes, then burns their villages.','Karenni villagers in burned village','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-06_3.jpg','This man was used as a porter by the dictators’ army and beaten. He escaped and was cared for by the Karen resistance. After receiving medical treatment he began his journey home. On the way he was captured and killed by the Burma Army in a betel nut grove.','Escaped porter','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-06_4.jpg','Village burned by the Burma Army on 27 April, 2006, Taw Ko Toe Baw, Muthraw District, Karen State.','Burned village of Taw Ko Toe Baw.','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-06_5.jpg','Families Displaced in Eastern Burma.','Displaced families','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-06_6.jpg','Cooking pot and cover destroyed by the Burma Army to terrorize villagers and drive them from their homes.','Cooking pot destroyed by Burma Army','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-07_1.jpg','Aung San Suu Kyi, a Nobel Peace Prize Laureate, has now spent over 11 years under house arrest. She is the leader of the National League for Democracy (NLD), the party which won over 80% of the vote in the 1990 elections in Burma. The military dictatorship responded by ignoring the results of the elections and jailing members of the opposition.','Aung San Suu Kyi','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-07_2.jpg','Villagers in Nyaunglebin District forced to build a fence around their village and the new Burma Army camp nearby.','Villagers forced to fence their own village','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-07_3.jpg','Some of the 850 people forced to carry supplies for the Burma Army Division 66.','Forced porters for BA Div 66','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-07_4.jpg','Burma Army Division 66 soldier recording the names of the forced laborers.','Burma Army office recording forced laborers','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-07_5.jpg','Naw Baby, a Karen nurse, age 22 years, captured by the Burma Army and now serving an eight-year sentence. Naw Baby is the second lady from the right, wearing red. Before she was captured she and the other nurses had said, “We are afraid of the Burma Army, but we want to help our people and our Karen Nation, so we try.” Please pray for this young woman and her freedom.','Captured Karen nurse, Naw Baby, in red','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-08_1.jpg','Kachin relief team member carries displaced Karen child.','Kachin relief team member carries child','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-08_2.jpg','Shan relief team provides medical treatment,\r\nT-shirts and encouragement to Shan villagers.','Shan relief team member','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-08_3.jpg','Lahu relief team provides dental aid to displaced\r\nLahu villagers in Shan State.','Lahu relief team member','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-09_1.jpg','A seventeen-year-old girl raped for two days by three Burma Army soldiers, 16-17 May 2006.','17 year old rape victim','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-09_2.jpg','This Shan family fled their village in Shan State where they had been forced to work for the Burma Army under brutal conditions. The father was addicted to opium and the mother to amphetamines. They told us the Burma Army gave them drugs as payment and to keep them under control. They are now recovering in a Shan State Army controlled area of Shan State.','Shan family in recovery.','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-09_3.jpg','Mway Khan (name changed), a young Shan girl who was raped by a Burma Army soldier. She was 9 years old at the time and is deeply traumatized and still suffering from the violent rape. Her family fled to a displaced persons site after the rape. The rape occurred in Ho Mong, Southeastern Shan State. A Shan FBR team helped this girl and her family escape last year. She is 10 years old now.','Shan rape victim','FBR','','','','',''),('','2006-05-30','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-09_4.jpg','Massacre of 16 Shan villagers on 22 October 1996, Ho Yan Village, Khun Hing District. Remains found on 30 May 2006.','Evidence of massacre in Shan State','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-09_5.jpg','Nang Sap, captured by the Burma Army when she was 5 years old, has been missing for seven years. She is reported dead, sacrificed at the Ho Mong temple by Burma Army troops.','Nang Sap, missing and reported dead','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-10_1.jpg','[<i>excerpt from <b>A Letter from a Relief Team Leader, 6 May 2006</b></i>]<br>\r\nYesterday we lost one of our best men due to a landmine placed by the Burma Army. His name was Saw Mu (Mr. Happy). We called him Mr. Afraid because he was not. He was the Muthraw District FBR team video cameraman. He was the team counselor and volunteered for additional duty, with the Good Life Club’s children programs. He was a bright, humble and brave young man. We are saddened by his death but believe he did not die in vain and was the finest example of Karen manhood. His was a full life of giving to many and he set an example of servant leadership. He died putting a light on the current Burma Army attacks on civilians and that light is shining.','Saw Mu 1983-2006','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-10_2.jpg','Saw Mya Win<br>\r\n(Died while serving displaced people in his home, Toungoo District, Northwestern Karen State.)','Mya Win  documents road crossing','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-10_3.jpg','The Face of Relief<br>\r\nOne year ago, medics found this boy with a badly burned face. After initial treatment from the medics and additional treatment at a nearby mobile clinic, the boy is now completely healed.','Burned child with mother','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-10_4.jpg','The Face of Relief<br>\r\nOne year ago, medics found this boy with a badly burned face. After initial treatment from the medics and additional treatment at a nearby mobile clinic, the boy is now completely healed.','Burned child after recovery','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-10_5.jpg','<font size=small>This letter was found placed next to a concealed Burma Army landmine. The following text was found on a similar sign found later, that was also placed next to a concealed Burma Army landmine.<br><br></font>\r\nFrom Burma Army:<br>\r\n“For the hiding villagers”\r\n(1) No one is allowed to live in this area.\r\n(2) People must move to Muthey or beside the car road at the relocation site as soon as possible, by 5 May.\r\n(3) Our troops do not want to shoot and capture.\r\n(4) By this date (5 May) anyone who stays in this area will be shot. This is a command from above.\r\n(5) You can come back when this area has peace.\r\n(6) Karen soldiers, do not do work that God and angels don’t like such as putting landmines and setting ambushes. Make peace and live together happily with your family.\r\n','Notes found near Burma Army landmines','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-12_1.jpg','Thank you for your prayers and for your stand with the people of Burma.<br>\r\nGod Bless you,<br>\r\nA Relief Team Leader<br>\r\nFree Burma Rangers','Relief worker carrying a displaced child running away from Burma Army attacks.','FBR','','','','',''),('','','SELF','1','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-12_2.jpg','It is not easy to trust God with all of our hearts, especially when we suffer. But there is no other way to live with faith than to give God our whole hearts no matter what each of us are facing wherever we are. May we give ourselves wholeheartedly to God as He leads us on.','Displaced villagers praying in a hiding place during a rainstorm.','FBR','','','','','');
