 a Burma \r\nArmy landmine while trying to help his \r\nfamily. They have had to &#64258;ee over twelve \r\ntimes and he is here now worshipping \r\nGod in church at a new village he and \r\nother families built together.  \r\nJanuary ‘09','Grandfather in IDP site','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/Health and anatomy class for displaced children at new villa.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','The sound of mortars is normal and the threat \r\nof attack is constant for the people in this part \r\nof eastern Burma. Civil war has torn normal life \r\napart for over 60 years in northern Karen State, \r\nBurma. \r\n<p>\r\nBut now, on this day, in this village, the war \r\nseems far away. The sun shines down out of a \r\ncloudless blue sky. This is the scene in village after village as FBR team members  \r\nlead the Good Life Club (GLC) and medical \r\nprograms. \r\nThere is joy and fun on their faces and this is \r\nsoon re?ected in not only the children’s faces, \r\nbut in the shouts and laughter coming from the \r\non-looking parents.','Health and anatomy class for  displaced children at new village.  December ‘08','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/Heavy mining in Kachin State.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','A consortium of Korean and Indian companies \r\ntogether with the SPDC is planning to construct \r\na pipeline over 1,100 km long from the Shwe \r\nnatural gas ?elds in the Bay of Bengal near Sittwe \r\nin Arakan State to Kunming in China. There are \r\nwidespread fears this will lead not only to vast \r\namounts of money going into the regime’s funds, \r\nbut also widespread human rights abuses as \r\npeople are displaced from the pipeline’s route. \r\nThere are also plans to dam the Salween River \r\nat several points in Karen State, again displacing \r\nthousands of villagers who will receive no bene?t \r\nfrom the projects. Deforestation is also of serious \r\nconcern, as is the mining of minerals such as jade \r\nin Kachin State with widespread environmental \r\ndamage.','Mining in Kachin State allowed  by the Burma Army. ‘09','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/IDPs Childern79.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','','A group of internally displaced  children in Arakan State, Burma.  August ‘09','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/Karen Elder, Saw Maw La, prays at New Year prayer service.jp.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','Grandfather Maw La, a Karen elder praying \r\nfor his congregation and all the people of \r\nBurma, Karen State.  December ‘09 \r\n<p>\r\n<i>\r\n“Is not this the kind of fasting I have chosen: \r\nto loose the chains of injustice and untie the \r\ncords of the yoke, to set the oppressed free \r\nand break every yoke?” Isaiah 58:6\r\n</i>','Karen Elder, Saw Maw La, prays at New Year prayer service','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/Karen resistance providing security.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','The resistance and villagers work together to \r\nslow down and in some cases even stop Burma \r\nArmy attacks. The ability of the people in the \r\nareas under attack to continue to survive and \r\nthrive is amazing. With very little or no outside \r\nsupport they hide their food supplies, prepare \r\nhiding places, ?nd food where they can, raise \r\nand educate their children and rebuild their \r\nhomes and villages when the Burma Army \r\n?nishes its operations. When the Burma Army \r\ntroops have passed by and are out of the \r\nimmediate area (although they still may be only \r\na few hours away on foot), the people go back \r\nto their ?elds, barns and houses to gather any \r\nfood supplies or belongings they can. They also \r\ngo to hiding places where they have stored food \r\nfor such an emergency. The people are prepared \r\nyear-round to ?ee, hide and survive.','Karen resistance providing security during a road crossing. January \'09','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/Karenni relief team trains to give IV and injections.jpg.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','','Karenni relief team trains to give IV and injections','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/Ler Per Her copy.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','Burma Army forces and their proxies attacked Ler \r\nPer Her IDP site in June 2009, driving over 1,000 \r\npeople from their homes and across the border \r\ninto Thailand. Homes were burned down and the \r\nschool destroyed.','Burma map showing Ler Per Her (Karen State)','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/Monkey prays for two killed by Burma Army with survivor.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','We all call him Monkey although his real name is \r\nK’Paw Say. He is a Karenni refugee, is co-leader of \r\nthe Free Burma Rangers and is the headquarters \r\ngroup pastor and video man. Monkey is \r\nresponsible for the training of all FBR video and \r\ncamera team members and for the spiritual life \r\nof all the teams.  He is a devout follower of Jesus \r\nand is close to all the team members; Christian, \r\nAnimist and Buddhist.','Monkey praying with woman whose  mother and brother were killed by the  Burma Army.','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/Monkey Relief team pastor and video man documenting Burma Ar.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','We all call him Monkey although his real name is \r\nK’Paw Say. He is a Karenni refugee, is co-leader of \r\nthe Free Burma Rangers and is the headquarters \r\ngroup pastor and video man. Monkey is \r\nresponsible for the training of all FBR video and \r\ncamera team members and for the spiritual life \r\nof all the teams.  He is a devout follower of Jesus \r\nand is close to all the team members; Christian, \r\nAnimist and Buddhist.','Monkey, Relief team pastor and video man, documenting Burma Army camp.','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/Monkey sick on IV and coordinating relief on Satphone during.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','We all call him Monkey although his real name is \r\nK’Paw Say. He is a Karenni refugee, is co-leader of \r\nthe Free Burma Rangers and is the headquarters \r\ngroup pastor and video man. Monkey is \r\nresponsible for the training of all FBR video and \r\ncamera team members and for the spiritual life \r\nof all the teams.  He is a devout follower of Jesus \r\nand is close to all the team members; Christian, \r\nAnimist and Buddhist.','Monkey coordinating relief efforts during attacks  while sick.','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/Monkey training new relief teams in camera techniques.jpg.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','We all call him Monkey although his real name is \r\nK’Paw Say. He is a Karenni refugee, is co-leader of \r\nthe Free Burma Rangers and is the headquarters \r\ngroup pastor and video man. Monkey is \r\nresponsible for the training of all FBR video and \r\ncamera team members and for the spiritual life \r\nof all the teams.  He is a devout follower of Jesus \r\nand is close to all the team members; Christian, \r\nAnimist and Buddhist.','Monkey training new relief teams in camera techniques','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/Monkey.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','We all call him Monkey although his real name is \r\nK’Paw Say. He is a Karenni refugee, is co-leader of \r\nthe Free Burma Rangers and is the headquarters \r\ngroup pastor and video man. Monkey is \r\nresponsible for the training of all FBR video and \r\ncamera team members and for the spiritual life \r\nof all the teams.  He is a devout follower of Jesus \r\nand is close to all the team members; Christian, \r\nAnimist and Buddhist.','Monkey, Relief team pastor and FBR co-leader','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/mother shot in face 09.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','','Ma Kin Kyi,  a 34-year-old nursing mother, shot  by the DKBA and Burma Army forces. Aug 09','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/Mya Win with his daughter before he died on 27 May 2006.jpg.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','','Mya Win, FBR relief team member, with his daughter before he died on 27 May 2006','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/FBR in rice field.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','','Relief teams and supplies moving to areas recently under attack. January ‘09','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/P1000896.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','','Sister of 14 year old boy, Nah Eh Moo,  \"My brother was too young and ran the wrong way and  they killed him.\"  December ‘0','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/P1010913.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','','Grandfather Maw La, a Karen elder praying  for his congregation and all the people of  Burma, Karen State.  December ‘09','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/P1040452.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','Burma Army forces and their proxies attacked Ler \r\nPer Her IDP site in June 2009, driving over 1,000 \r\npeople from their homes and across the border \r\ninto Thailand. Homes were burned down and the \r\nschool destroyed.','Annual Global Day of Prayer for Burma in Ler Per Her before the June \'09 attacks.','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/PA300615.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','','Shan relief teams provide medical  treatment. ‘09','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/refchild.jpg','','','','PRAD','','1','','SELF','Burma Army forces and their proxies attacked Ler \r\nPer Her IDP site in June 2009, driving over 1,000 \r\npeople from their homes and across the border \r\ninto Thailand. Homes were burned down and the \r\nschool destroyed.','Families fleeing   Ler Per Her. June ‘09 (PRAD)','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/refugees fleeing ler per her camp.jpg','','','','PRAD','','1','','SELF','Burma Army forces and their proxies attacked Ler \r\nPer Her IDP site in June 2009, driving over 1,000 \r\npeople from their homes and across the border \r\ninto Thailand. Homes were burned down and the \r\nschool destroyed.','Families fleeing   Ler Per Her. June ‘09 (PRAD)','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/Saw Brave Naw Paw Di Htoo with mothers and family.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','The ethnic people of Burma continue one of the most \r\npositive acts of civil disobedience in this oppressed country. \r\nThey are building up their people, culture, land \r\nand freedom. \r\nThe story of Naw Moo Eh and Naw Rosemary is the story of two young mothers \r\nwho choose to live with their families in an area \r\nunder direct Burma Army threat, and illustrates the \r\ndetermination, faith and ability of the people. \r\n<p>\r\n<i>\r\n“We had no food and no security. We went \r\nback on faith alone.”\r\n</i>\r\n<p>\r\nPlease see the Global Day of Prayer for Burma 2010 brochure for the full story.','Naw Moo Eh and Naw Rosemary with their children.  January ‘09','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/Security and documentation of road crossing April 06.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','While on a relief mission in Toungoo District, \r\nnorthern Karen State, Mya Win, FBR team video \r\nman and reporter, died of malaria as he helped \r\nhis people ?ee the attacking Burma Army. He \r\nstayed behind with the people even as he was \r\nsick.  At the height of the rainy season, with no \r\ngood shelter, little food and giving his all to care \r\nfor the displaced families, Mya Win lost his life on \r\nMay 27, 2006.','Mya Win on a mission. March ‘06','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/sHAN AND kAREN BAPTISM.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','','Karen young people  and a Shan relief team leader prepare to  be baptized.  April ‘09','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/shan chin and karen medics.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','','Shan, Chin and Karen medics treat patients.  December ‘08','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/Shot soldier treated by medic.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','In ethnic areas the Burma Army builds roads to \r\nproject their power more rapidly through the \r\narea. The roads serve the army camps from which \r\nattacks are launched and serve as formidable \r\nbarriers to people trying to cross them. The \r\nroads cut through farms and villages, displacing \r\nall people along their axis, and separating \r\ncommunities from each other. The roads are \r\npatrolled and mined by the Burma Army and \r\nare barriers to travel, trade and the sending of \r\nrelief.','Karen soldier, shot by the Burma Army while helping villagers to cross the road,  being treated by a medic.','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/soldier watches as porter carries water to camp.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','The Burma Army continues \r\nto force villagers in Burma \r\nto work for them on road \r\nprojects, carrying supplies, \r\nand building Burma Army \r\ncamps. The Burma Army \r\nalso forces villagers to act as \r\nhuman minesweepers to clear \r\nthe roads ahead of them.  The \r\ncontinual build-up of forces \r\nby the Burma Army and the \r\ninfrastructure to support \r\nthese forces is a burden on \r\nthe villagers and results in \r\nincreased oppression for all \r\nthe people of Burma.','Burma Army soldier  watches as villager is forced to carry  water to his camp, Karen State, January ‘09','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/Villagers reading DOP.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','','Villagers reading about the Global  Day of Prayer for Burma.  December ‘08','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/wood truck.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','The Burma Army continues \r\nto force villagers in Burma \r\nto work for them on road \r\nprojects, carrying supplies, \r\nand building Burma Army \r\ncamps. The Burma Army \r\nalso forces villagers to act as \r\nhuman minesweepers to clear \r\nthe roads ahead of them.  The \r\ncontinual build-up of forces \r\nby the Burma Army and the \r\ninfrastructure to support \r\nthese forces is a burden on \r\nthe villagers and results in \r\nincreased oppression for all \r\nthe people of Burma.','Burma Army soldiers stand  guard on logging project, Karen  State, Burma.  April ‘09','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/WWII Veteran  26 Dec 08.jpgSaw.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','<b>“We tried our  \r\nbest to help them,  \r\nnow we are in difficulty,  \r\nwe wonder if they  \r\nwill help us”</b>\r\n<p>\r\n“In World War II, the Japanese invaded here and \r\ndrove the British out. They killed and tortured us \r\na lot. If they wanted to kill one of us Karen, they \r\njust did it. We worked with the British to help \r\nthem ?ght the Japanese. They asked us to help \r\nthem and we did. 160 of us joined the British: 80 \r\nof us as local militia or home guard, and 80 as a \r\nmobile unit to ?ght alongside the British on their \r\noperations.\r\nWe tried our best to help them (the British and \r\nallies), now we are in difficulty, we wonder if they \r\nwill help us.”\r\n<p>-- WWII veteran, Saw Nya They Mu','WWII veteran, Saw Nya They Mu, 80  years old. Muthraw District, Northern Karen State, Burma.   December ‘08','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/P_Saw Paw and daughter Moon Moon Win 2007.jpg.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','<i>“My husband died for his people, I will take his place on the FBR team.”</i>\r\n<p>-- P’Saw Paw (Dew Flower), age 26, \r\nwidow and mother of a 4 year  \r\nold daughter. P\'Saw Paw is the widow of FBR Ranger Mya Win who died of malaria in 2006.','P Saw Paw and daughter Moon Moon Win 2007','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/P_Saw Paw at the camp in Oct 2009.jpg.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','<i>“My husband died for his people, I will take his place on the FBR team.”</i>\r\n<p>-- P’Saw Paw (Dew Flower), age 26, \r\nwidow and mother of a 4 year  \r\nold daughter. P\'Saw Paw is the widow of FBR Ranger Mya Win who died of malaria in 2006.','P Saw Paw at the FBR training camp in Oct 2009','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/20090723 Saw Eh K_ Nyaw 7 old.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','Child and Woman shot by Dictator\'s forces. The \r\nDemocratic Karen Buddhist Army (DKBA), a proxy force of \r\nthe Burma Army, together with the Burma Army shot five \r\nvillagers in Bray Day (also known as Paw Ler Loh) village, \r\neastern Karen State, killing one of them.','Saw Eh K Nyaw, child shot by Dictator\'s forces','','',''),('/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2010/Pictures/500/saw-ko-tro_s-wife-and-siste.jpg','','','','FBR','','1','','SELF','','Women check their belongings after fleeing a  Burma Army attack, Karen State, Burma.  December ‘08','','','');
