INSERT INTO `idx_idx_prayer_day_of_prayer_2013_images_slideshow_400_7992` VALUES ('FBR','','1','','SELF','','Relief supplies on the way','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/Relief supplies on the way_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','I am a medic working with Free Burma Rangers based in the \r\nJungle School of Medicine Kawthoolei (JSM-K). Since I was \r\nsmall, I have been interested in medicine. When teachers \r\nused to ask me, “What do you want to be?” I used to say, “A \r\ndoctor.” During the many years of civil war in Burma, the \r\nKaren people have had poor access to health care. There are \r\nsimply not enough health workers. The few we have do not \r\nhave the chance to study medicine to a very high level. So \r\nmany Karen people die from causes that are simple to treat.  --Toh Win, Medic at JSM-K','Toh Win','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/Toh Picture_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','Karen State, Burma: The tarp hangs loosely, strung up \r\nbetween two crooked goalposts. On it is a hand-drawn \r\nmap of Burma. Some 300 children sit on the ground, \r\nlooking at this map of their country. At least, we tell \r\nthem it is their country – they know it as Burma, while \r\ntheir country is “Kawthoolei” and both are distinct \r\nnations.','Burma soldiers in trenches and bunker with machine gun','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/5 Burma soldiers in trenches and bunker with machine gun_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','On 2 May 2012, Aung San Suu Kyi was sworn into Parliament in a historic session in \r\nwhich the long-time opposition leader and political prisoner officially became part of \r\nthe democratic process for which she has fought for so long. Her decision to contest the \r\nelections at the lower level of Parliament denoted her acceptance of the process towards \r\npeace being implemented by the current central government - though there is still \r\nwidespread uncertainty and speculation about President Thein Sein’s motives and ability \r\nto implement true democracy.','Aung San Suu Kyi','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/ASSK_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','Karen State, Burma: The tarp hangs loosely, strung up \r\nbetween two crooked goalposts. On it is a hand-drawn \r\nmap of Burma. Some 300 children sit on the ground, \r\nlooking at this map of their country. At least, we tell \r\nthem it is their country – they know it as Burma, while \r\ntheir country is “Kawthoolei” and both are distinct \r\nnations.','Arakan dance performance at a Good Life Club','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/Arakan Dance_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','','Keepsakes litter the remains of an IDP house overrun by the Burma Army','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/kachin grad photo_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','','ai Nawng playing with children at a GLC program in \r\nKaren State','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/Arakan Surviving Children at IDP Camp_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','Sai Nawng is the coordinator for all of FBR’s Shan \r\nteams. He first came to FBR in 2004, came back and \r\nbecame a team leader and soon was the coordinator \r\nfor all the Shan teams.','Sai Nawng prays at a GLC program in Shan State','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/Sai nong_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','Many families live on very basic foods: rice, \r\nvegetables, chilies and salt. On special occasions \r\nthey may have meat. Decide with your family \r\nto prepare and eat a ‘meal of prayer’ for ethnic \r\npeople in Burma.','Finding ways to respond to the need in Burma','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/context7_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','','On 2 May 2012, Aung San Suu Kyi was sworn into Parliament in a historic session in \r\nwhich the long-time opposition leader and political prisoner officially became part of \r\nthe democratic process for which she has fought for so long. Her decision to contest the \r\nelections at the lower level of Parliament denoted her acceptance of the process towards \r\npeace being implemented by the current central government - though there is still \r\nwidespread uncertainty and speculation about President Thein Sein’s motives and ability \r\nto implement true democracy.','Arakan team leads Good lIfe Program for Karen children in Karen State','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/Arakan team leads Good lIfe Program for Karen children in Karen State.jpg','','','','','',''),('CCB','','1','','SELF','“Sha” was 8 years old and on her way to school when mushrooms caught her eye. \r\nAs she stepped off of the path to pick some, the landmine exploded and her life \r\nwas forever changed. Sha lost her right leg almost to her hip. That was nearly nine \r\nyears ago and she has grown from a little girl to a young woman, unable to run \r\nand play with others.','Sha and others cross the border to recieve prosthetics','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/Sha prepares to come across_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','','Children eating dinner after GLC program.','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/CIBGLC dinner (2) - Copy_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','','Mon relief team sings for Karen villagers during Good \r\nLife Club','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/CIBMon team at GLC.jpg_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','','Kids at a GLC program','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/CIBglc (4)_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','','Hsa Kae helping a patient.','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/CIBhsa kae_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','On 3 July 2012, Kyar Shell, Lahu relief team leader, \r\ndied of liver failure while on a mission. He leaves \r\nbehind his wife and young son. On 28 March 2012, Saw Kler Lay was killed by a \r\nlightning strike during a heavy thunderstorm. He was \r\nworking inside Burma in his home area of Karen State. On 6 March 2012, eight months into a long-range \r\nrelief mission, Hsaw Reh drowned while crossing the \r\nPon River in central Karenni State. He had been on \r\nhis way to pick up a supply of medicine so his team \r\ncould continue their mission.','In Memoriam','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/cross silhouette dark people_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','Many families live on very basic foods: rice, \r\nvegetables, chilies and salt. On special occasions \r\nthey may have meat. Decide with your family \r\nto prepare and eat a ‘meal of prayer’ for ethnic \r\npeople in Burma.','Children from four villages run in the run for relief at Tha Da Der, site of the burned church.','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/CIBrun for relief in burned village.jupg_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('CCB','','1','','SELF','“Sha” was 8 years old and on her way to school when mushrooms caught her eye. \r\nAs she stepped off of the path to pick some, the landmine exploded and her life \r\nwas forever changed. Sha lost her right leg almost to her hip. That was nearly nine \r\nyears ago and she has grown from a little girl to a young woman, unable to run \r\nand play with others.','Sha, laughing after receiving her new leg.','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/Copy of Sha gives thanks crop_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','So often, when we have given the best \r\nwe have, it still is not enough. But God sees, and comes alongside us, and \r\nbrings His own hand of healing into our little hospital and the lives of our \r\npatients. And for that we are grateful. --Dr. Kaw, \r\nTeacher at Jungle School of Medicine -- Kawthoolei','Staff medic gives oxygen to a baby with pneumonia at the','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/DOP pneumonia baby_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','','Relief team medics from JSM-K on a mission.','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/DSC_0061_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','','FBR medic and high school student teach health with the anatomy apron.','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/DSC_0138_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','','FBR medic prescribes glasses','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/DSC_0203_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','','Good Life Club program.','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/DSC_0226_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','I am a medic working with Free Burma Rangers based in the \r\nJungle School of Medicine Kawthoolei (JSM-K). Since I was \r\nsmall, I have been interested in medicine. When teachers \r\nused to ask me, “What do you want to be?” I used to say, “A \r\ndoctor.” During the many years of civil war in Burma, the \r\nKaren people have had poor access to health care. There are \r\nsimply not enough health workers. The few we have do not \r\nhave the chance to study medicine to a very high level. So \r\nmany Karen people die from causes that are simple to treat.  --Toh Win, Medic at JSM-K','Student at GLC program, identifying Shan State on map of Burma 400','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/Student at GLC program, identifying Shan State on map of Burma_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','','Chin relief team member checks a patient.','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/During treatment boy at lotharawn village. he have stomach ache._400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','On 6 March 2012, eight months into a long-range \r\nrelief mission, Hsaw Reh drowned while crossing the \r\nPon River in central Karenni State. He had been on \r\nhis way to pick up a supply of medicine so his team \r\ncould continue their mission. Hsaw Reh was 23. We \r\nare saddened by his death and extend our love and \r\nsorrow to his family, his team and his people. His \r\nloss will be greatly felt not just by all of us but also \r\nby those people he served so faithfully. To Hsaw Reh \r\nwe want to say, “Thank you and we thank God for \r\nyou. You were a good teammate and you served your \r\npeople well – you are an honor to your family, your \r\nteam and your people and we are blessed to have \r\nknown you.','Hsaw Reh','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/Hsaw Rey (4)_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','On 6 March 2012, eight months into a long-range \r\nrelief mission, Hsaw Reh drowned while crossing the \r\nPon River in central Karenni State. He had been on \r\nhis way to pick up a supply of medicine so his team \r\ncould continue their mission. Hsaw Reh was 23. We \r\nare saddened by his death and extend our love and \r\nsorrow to his family, his team and his people. His \r\nloss will be greatly felt not just by all of us but also \r\nby those people he served so faithfully. To Hsaw Reh \r\nwe want to say, “Thank you and we thank God for \r\nyou. You were a good teammate and you served your \r\npeople well – you are an honor to your family, your \r\nteam and your people and we are blessed to have \r\nknown you.','Mon, Lahu and Karen rangers sing in Karen State GLC program','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/glc good luthaw (5)_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','','Interior of an IDP house','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/IDP interior - 2010-07-20 at 14-36-00BW_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','On 28 March 2012, Saw Kler Lay was killed by a \r\nlightning strike during a heavy thunderstorm. He was \r\nworking inside Burma in his home area of Karen State. \r\nKler Lay was a video cameraman as well as a deputy \r\nteam leader, and he had been serving his people on a \r\nrelief team since 2008. He was tough, smart and kind, \r\nand always willing to help and encourage others. He \r\nset an example of love, service, perseverance and \r\nprofessionalism that reflects great credit on him, \r\nhis people, the FBR and the KNU.','Karenni team medic treating a patient in Karenni State.','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/Karennni_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','On 28 March 2012, Saw Kler Lay was killed by a \r\nlightning strike during a heavy thunderstorm. He was \r\nworking inside Burma in his home area of Karen State. \r\nKler Lay was a video cameraman as well as a deputy \r\nteam leader, and he had been serving his people on a \r\nrelief team since 2008. He was tough, smart and kind, \r\nand always willing to help and encourage others. He \r\nset an example of love, service, perseverance and \r\nprofessionalism that reflects great credit on him, \r\nhis people, the FBR and the KNU.','Kler Lay','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/Kler lay_400.jpg','','','','','',''),('FBR','','1','','SELF','On 3 July 2012, Kyar Shell, Lahu relief team leader, \r\ndied of liver failure while on a mission. He leaves \r\nbehind his wife and young son. He is loved and will \r\nbe missed by his family, his team and the people he \r\ndied serving. He was trained in 2004 and served with \r\ngreat dedication until his death. Kyar Shell was a \r\npioneering team leader, leading the first Lahu team in \r\na challenging and dangerous area of Shan State. His \r\nefforts resulted in saved lives and needed relief for \r\nthousands of Lahu and Shan people. He was a calm, \r\nhumble man with keen insight and compassion and \r\na man of action who took great risks to help people \r\nin need and never sought fame or glory.','Kyar Shell','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/Kyar shell GLCBW_400.jpg','','','','','',''