INSERT INTO `idx_idx_reports_5366` VALUES ('','2005-04-23','','CCB','','1','','SELF','Information about the 2005 Run for Relief in Chiang Mai, Thailand','2005 Run for Relief information','/IDX/Get_Involved/20050321_run_info.htm','','',''),('','2002-02-01','','BBC','','1','','SELF','BBC special on the plight of the Karen in Burma.','PI for the Correspondent: The Forgotten People','/IDX/Reports/2002/hrr_bbc.html','','',''),('','2007-07-17','','AWSJ','','1','','SELF','A Regime Change in Burma<br>\r\n\r\nBy BENEDICT ROGERS <br>\r\nArticle in the July 17, 2002 Asian Wall Street Journal','A Regime Change in Burma','/IDX/Reports/2002/rogers_7_02.html','','',''),('','2003-10-01','','www.house.gov','','1','','SELF','Statement of Congressman Joseph R. Pitts<br>\r\nnternational Relations Subcommittee on Terrorism, Nonproliferation and Human Rights','Human Rights in Burma: Fifteen Years Post Military Coup','/IDX/Reports/2003/joseph_pitts_statement.html','','',''),('','2003-05-18','','CSW','','1','','SELF','Report by Benedict Rogers of Christian Solidarity Worldwide(CSW)','Visit to the Thai-Burmese border','/IDX/Reports/2003/rogers_04_03.html','','',''),('Naw Moo Day Wa and Naw Sa Sakee Wa','2006-01-09','','FBR','','1','','SELF','These two 12 year old girls are displaced Karen whose homes weredestroyed by the Burma Army. They now live in an IDP site in the Northern Karen State of Burma. They are also now the charter members of the Good Life Club-\"God brings good life\", in this area.','Message from a Relief Team Leader','/IDX/Reports/2006/20060106.html','','',''),('','2006-01-08','','CCB','','1','','SELF','A Free Burma Housewife Reports from the Mae Tao Clinic','Thu Zar Aung and Aung Aung','/IDX/Reports/2006/20060108_aung_aung.html','','',''),('','2006-01-11','','CCB','','1','','SELF','Announcement about the Global Day of Prayer for Burma, 2006','Global Day of Prayer for Burma 2006','/IDX/Reports/2006/20060111.html','','',''),('','2006-01-18','','FBR','','1','','SELF','The lady in the photo is named Naw Rutha, she gave birth to a baby boy in the first week of December. One week later the Burma Army came to attack and she and the other villagers fled.','A Mother\'s Story from Burma','/IDX/Reports/2006/20060118.html','','',''),('','2006-01-16','','FBR','','1','','SELF','These photos were taken in Hee Daw Kaw Village in Northern Karen State in January 2006. Hee Daw Kaw was attacked in late November 2005 by Burma Army Infantry Battalion 75.','Pictures of Burned Village in Northern Karen State, Burma','/IDX/Reports/2006/20060120.html','','',''),('','2006-03-14','','FBR','','1','','SELF','Dear Friends of the Wa, Thank you so much to all of you who care for the Wa and have helped so generously. We thank God too for Kay Orsini who is the new volunteer coordinator for the Wa work here. ','Wa Outreach in Thailand – Annual Report 2005 Frontier Mission Project of the Presbyterian Church (USA)','/IDX/Reports/2006/20060314.html','','',''),('','2006-03-16','','CCB','','1','','SELF','Wa Outreach in Thailand – Annual Report 2006','Wa Outreach in Thailand – Annual Report 2006','/IDX/Reports/2006/20060316_wa1.html','','',''),('','2006-03-16','','CCB','','1','','SELF','These 3 photo attachments are additions to the Wa 2006 Report sent separately.','Photos from the Wa Outreach in Thailand','/IDX/Reports/2006/20060316_wa2.html','','',''),('','2007-02-04','','CCB','','1','','SELF','Christians Concerned for Burma along with Partners Relief & Development is\r\nhosting an event called \"³80 Hours of Prayer for Burma\" to take place in an\r\non-site prayer room in Chiang Mai beginning at noon on Thursday, February\r\n15th through till Sunday, February 18th, 2007, at which time we will close\r\nthe event with a gathering in the prayer room from 6-8pm to pray and worship\r\ntogether.','80 Hours of Prayer for Burma','/IDX/Reports/2007/20070204.html','','',''),('','2007-09-22','','CCB','','1','','SELF','There has been a request from inside Burma urging people of all faiths to join in a prayer vigil for for the next three days.','An Urgent Call for Prayer','/IDX/Reports/2007/20070922.html','','',''),('','2007-10-04','','CCB','','1','','SELF','Video announcement: On the front line of conflict deep inside Burma this documentary follows ethnic relief workers as they aid internally displaced people suffering under the Burma Army.','Prayer of Peace: Relief & Resistance in Burma\'s War Zones','/IDX/Reports/2007/20071004.html','','',''),('','2007-10-04','','CCB','','1','','SELF','Thousands of Christians began a fast throughout Burma on Wednesday to pray\r\nfor the release of arrested pro-democracy protesters and for peace to\r\nprevail in Burma.','Christians in Burma pray for peace and release of detainees - Saw Yan Naing','/IDX/Reports/2007/20071008.html','','',''),('','2007-10-15','','CCB','','1','','SELF','This is from a nurse, Cindy, who helped us train new Shan medics in a border area last month. I hope her message is an encouragement to you,','Message From a Nurse','/IDX/Reports/2007/20071015.php','','',''),('','2007-10-23','','CCB','','1','','SELF','Thank you for all that you do and for making these two hostels possible -- the Lawa (Wa) Student hostel in Chiang Mai, Thailand (photos 1, 4, 5 and 6) and the Ying Phang Hostel in Wa State, Burma (photos 2 and 3). We thank God for you and the pull he has placed on your heart to support this work.','The Lawa Mission: A Report In Pictures','/IDX/Reports/2007/20071023.html','','',''),('','2007-11-16','','FBR','','1','','SELF','The chief and most powerful enemy of human beings is the deceiver of Adam and Eve, the serpent, our ancient foe that “seeks to work us woe.” It wants to destroy the image of God in the world. It wants to damage and destroy our bodies, our minds, our hearts and our souls. ','Fighting the Serpent by Praying for the Enemy','/IDX/Reports/2007/20071116.html','','',''),('','2007-11-30','','FBR','','1','','SELF','We wanted to share this letter with you. It is by a good friend from Partners Relief and Development, who help us in many ways including the training of the Good Life Club counselors that are on each Free Burma Ranger team.','Good Life Club Training','/IDX/Reports/2007/20071130.html','','',''),('','2008-03-21','','CCB','','1','','SELF','On March 9, 2008, people all over the world prayed for Burma on this the 11th \r\n  year of this global day of prayer. Report includes photographs from Karen State.','Global Day of Prayer for Burma 2008, a Report','/IDX/Reports/2008/20080321.html','','',''),('','2008-04-06','','FBR','','1','','SELF','Letter from Allan Eubank April 2008: After 50 years of waiting celebrating the first baptism of the Talako Karen','First Baptism of Talako Karen','/IDX/Reports/2008/20080406.html','','',''),('','2008-05-07','','CCB','','1','','SELF','We are now trying to partner with friends in Burma to help people affected \r\n  by the cyclone, where there are reports of over 20,000 dead, over 40,000 missing \r\n  and 1 million displaced.','Message about  the Cyclone in Burma','/IDX/Reports/2008/20080507.html','','',''),('','2008-05-09','','FBR','','1','','http://www.freeburmarangers.org/Reports/2008/20080509a.html','The cyclone death toll is now reported to be up to 100,000. The dictators of Burma are actively obstructing local as well as international relief efforts. Local organizations and churches are working in the affected area and doing their best to help survivors.','FBR REPORT: Update on Cyclone Relief Efforts, Photos of the Devastation','/IDX/Reports/2008/20080509.html','','',''),('','2008-05-14','','FBR','','1','','SELF','Thank you for your prayers, donations and concern for those suffering in Burma. The cyclone victims and those attacked and displaced by the Burma Army need and appreciate prayers and help.','Prayer request and Ongoing response to Cyclone','/IDX/Reports/2008/20080515.html','','',''),('','2009-03-06','','FBR','','1','','SELF','This year on Sunday, March 8, thousands of people from all over the world will join together in prayer for the people of Burma, on this, the 13th annual Global Day of Prayer for Burma.','13th Annual Global Day of Prayer for Burma, March 8 2009','/IDX/Reports/2009/20090306.html','','',''),('','2009-03-25','','FBR','','1','','SELF','Last week we had the first baptism of one our Shan FBR relief team leaders. ','Update from CCB','/IDX/Reports/2009/20090325.html','','',''),('','2009-03-31','','CCB','','1','','SELF','Thanks to all of you who prayed for Burma on March 8, 2009, the 13th annual Global Day of Prayer for Burma. The pictures in this report were taken at two services: one in Karen State where a group of displaced people gathered to pray','Pictures from the 2009 Global Day of Prayer for Burma','/IDX/Reports/2009/20090331.html','','',''),('','2009-05-01','','CCB','','1','','SELF','We thank you for continuing to care about and help the Wa people of northeastern Burma and their cousins, the Lawa of Thailand. The Wa Hills of Burma are marked on some maps of Southeast Asia, but even here in Chiang Mai in northern Thailand, they seem very far away','Wa Outreach in Thailand - Annual Report 2008','/IDX/Reports/2009/20090419.html','','',''),('','2010-03-13','','FBR','','1','','SELF','Here is a story written by a friend who is a Burma expert who recently accompanied us on a relief mission. It was encouraging to us and we hope it is encouraging to you as well.','Letter From a Friend','/IDX/Reports/2010/20100313 letter from a friend.html','','',''),('','2010-05-26','','FBR','','1','','SELF','Frontier Mission Project of the Presbyterian Church (USA) \r\n\r\nApril 8, 2010 ','Wa Outreach in Thailand - Annual Report 2009','/IDX/Reports/2010/20100526.html','','',''),('','2010-09-28','','CCB','','1','','SELF','A 50 year mission on the Thai-Burma border.\r\nRaised in Texas, Allan Eubank has been a missionary in Thailand since 1961. This short documentary is the story of his work with the Talako people. A story of faith, perseverance and victory in Jesus Christ.','New film documents a 50 year mission on the Thai/Burma border','/IDX/Reports/2010/20101001 mission to the talako.html','','',''),('','2001-01-10','','FBR','','1','','SELF','A description of the events surrounding the most important date in the Burmese democracy movement.','8 8 88','/IDX/Resources/Articles/8_8_88.html','','',''),('','2001-01-10','','CCB','','1','','SELF','Aung San Suu Kyi is the winner of a Nobel Peace Prize and leader of the democratically elected political party in Burma, the National League for Democracy (NLD). The military regime never recognized the results of the elections held in 1989 that were overwhelmingly in support of the NLD.','Aung San Suu Kyi','/IDX/Resources/Articles/aungsang.html','','',''),('SPDC, SLORC','2000-10-24','','CCB','','1','','SELF','Burma is a failed state under the rule of one of the world\'s most repressive regimes.  A description of the current governmental regime.','Burma\'s Dictators, Narcotics, and China','/IDX/Resources/Articles/burma_china.html','','',''),('','2001-01-10','','CCB','','1','','SELF','Due to the oppression of the dictators of Burma there are approximately 2million people inside Burma who have been displaced from their homes. An overview of the IDP situation in Burma.','Internally Displaced People of Burma','/IDX/Resources/Articles/idp.html','','',''),('','2001-01-10','','CCB','','1','','SELF','\"Please tell our friends in the world, thank you for praying for us. We pray for you too because we know you face your own troubles . . . \" Quotes from IDPs and refugees from Burma.','IDP Quotes','/IDX/Resources/Articles/idp_quotes.html','','',''),('','2001-01-10','','CCB','','1','','SELF','In spite of the attacks of the Burma Army the people of Burma have not given up. In the jungle mobile clinics provide care for victims of the Burma Army.','Medical Relief','/IDX/Resources/Articles/medical.html','','',''),('','2001-01-10','','CCB','','1','','SELF','The ethnic people of Burma as well as the Burman people continue their struggle for basic human rights, democracy, and freedom. An overview of the situation inside Burma.','Life Without Sanctuary','/IDX/Resources/Articles/no_sanctuary.html','','',''),('','2001-01-10','','CCB','','1','','SELF','Narcotic production and trafficking in Burma provides the SPDC with a major source of revenue. In 1999 alone, 1,750 tons of opium was grown and processed into heroin.','Wa and Narcotics','/IDX/Resources/Articles/wa_narcotics.html','','',''),('','2002-05-01','','SHRF & SWAN','','1','','http://www.shanland.org/resources/bookspub/humanrights/LtoR/','This report details 173 incidents of rape and other forms of sexual violence, involving 625 girls and women, committed by Burmese army troops in Shan State, mostly between 1996 and 2001.','Licence to Rape;The Burmese military regime ’s use of sexual violence in the ongoing war in Shan State.','/IDX/Resources/Books/license_to_rape.rpt','','',''),('','2012-02-23','','CCB','','1','','','Please join us in the 2012 Global Day of Prayer for Burma','Announcement for the 2012 Global Day of Prayer for Burma','/IDX/Reports/2012/20120223 DOP announcement.php','','',''),('','2012-08-29','','CCB','','1','','','We would like to pass on to you an invitation to tour Thailand with Allan and Joan Eubank as your hosts(parents of David Eubank of FBR).','Invitation to a Unique Tour of Thailand, 2013','/IDX/Reports/2012/20120829 Unique Tour.php','','',''),('','2013-04-24','','FBR','','1','','','Thank you to all who participated in the 2013 Global Day of Prayer for Burma','2013 Day of Prayer - Thank You from CCB','/IDX/Reports/2013/20130424 Day of Prayer Thank You.php','','',''),('','2013-12-31','','CCB','','1','','','Recently the Billy Graham Evangelistic\r\nAssociation (BGEA), held an Abundant Life Festival in Chiang Mai. Leading up\r\nto the festival I met with a friend named Eleanor who said, \"It would be\r\ngreat if some refugees could come to the event.\"','Refugees Sing for Abundant Life','/IDX/Reports/2013/20131231.php','','','');
