NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4806,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-07_4.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','Burma Army Division 66 soldier recording the names of the forced laborers.','','','2006-12-28 20:12:23','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4807,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-07_5.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 20:13:02','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4808,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-07_5.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','Naw Baby, a Karen nurse, age 22 years, captured by the Burma Army and now serving an eight-year sentence. Naw Baby is the second lady from the right, wearing red. Before she was captured she and the other nurses had said, “We are afraid of the Burma Army, but we want to help our people and our Karen Nation, so we try.” Please pray for this young woman and her freedom.','','','2006-12-28 20:13:02','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4809,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-08_1.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 20:13:27','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4810,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-08_1.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','Kachin relief team member carries displaced Karen child.','','','2006-12-28 20:13:27','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4811,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-08_2.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 20:13:44','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4812,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-08_2.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','Shan relief team provides medical treatment,\r\nT-shirts and encouragement to Shan villagers.','','','2006-12-28 20:13:44','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4813,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-08_3.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 20:14:04','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4814,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-08_3.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','Lahu relief team provides dental aid to displaced\r\nLahu villagers in Shan State.','','','2006-12-28 20:14:04','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4815,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-09_1.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 20:14:37','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4816,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-09_1.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','A seventeen-year-old girl raped for two days by three Burma Army soldiers, 16-17 May 2006.','','','2006-12-28 20:14:37','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4817,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-09_2.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 20:14:53','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4818,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-09_2.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','This Shan family fled their village in Shan State where they had been forced to work for the Burma Army under brutal conditions. The father was addicted to opium and the mother to amphetamines. They told us the Burma Army gave them drugs as payment and to keep them under control. They are now recovering in a Shan State Army controlled area of Shan State.','','','2006-12-28 20:14:53','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4819,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-09_3.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 20:15:05','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4820,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-09_3.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','Mway Khan (name changed), a young Shan girl who was raped by a Burma Army soldier. She was 9 years old at the time and is deeply traumatized and still suffering from the violent rape. Her family fled to a displaced persons site after the rape. The rape occurred in Ho Mong, Southeastern Shan State. A Shan FBR team helped this girl and her family escape last year. She is 10 years old now.','','','2006-12-28 20:15:05','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4821,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-09_4.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 20:15:21','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4822,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-09_4.jpg','idx1','Page','date','','','','','','','2006-12-28 20:15:21','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','2006-05-30'),(4823,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-09_4.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','Massacre of 16 Shan villagers on 22 October 1996, Ho Yan Village, Khun Hing District. Remains found on 30 May 2006.','','','2006-12-28 20:15:21','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4824,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-09_5.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 20:15:34','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4825,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-09_5.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','Nang Sap, captured by the Burma Army when she was 5 years old, has been missing for seven years. She is reported dead, sacrificed at the Ho Mong temple by Burma Army troops.','','','2006-12-28 20:15:34','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4826,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-10_1.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 00:44:13','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4827,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-10_1.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','[<i>excerpt from <b>A Letter from a Relief Team Leader, 6 May 2006</b></i>]<br>\r\nYesterday we lost one of our best men due to a landmine placed by the Burma Army. His name was Saw Mu (Mr. Happy). We called him Mr. Afraid because he was not. He was the Muthraw District FBR team video cameraman. He was the team counselor and volunteered for additional duty, with the Good Life Club’s children programs. He was a bright, humble and brave young man. We are saddened by his death but believe he did not die in vain and was the finest example of Karen manhood. His was a full life of giving to many and he set an example of servant leadership. He died putting a light on the current Burma Army attacks on civilians and that light is shining.','','','2006-12-28 20:54:34','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4828,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-10_2.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 00:46:48','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4829,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-10_2.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','Saw Mya Win<br>\r\n(Died while serving displaced people in his home, Toungoo District, Northwestern Karen State.)','','','2006-12-28 20:53:46','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4830,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-10_3.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 00:47:43','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4831,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-10_3.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','The Face of Relief<br>\r\nOne year ago, medics found this boy with a badly burned face. After initial treatment from the medics and additional treatment at a nearby mobile clinic, the boy is now completely healed.','','','2006-12-28 00:47:43','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4832,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-10_4.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 00:48:08','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4833,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-10_4.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','The Face of Relief<br>\r\nOne year ago, medics found this boy with a badly burned face. After initial treatment from the medics and additional treatment at a nearby mobile clinic, the boy is now completely healed.','','','2006-12-28 20:54:52','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4834,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-10_5.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 00:49:02','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4835,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-10_5.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','<font size=small>This letter was found placed next to a concealed Burma Army landmine. The following text was found on a similar sign found later, that was also placed next to a concealed Burma Army landmine.<br><br></font>\r\nFrom Burma Army:<br>\r\n“For the hiding villagers”\r\n(1) No one is allowed to live in this area.\r\n(2) People must move to Muthey or beside the car road at the relocation site as soon as possible, by 5 May.\r\n(3) Our troops do not want to shoot and capture.\r\n(4) By this date (5 May) anyone who stays in this area will be shot. This is a command from above.\r\n(5) You can come back when this area has peace.\r\n(6) Karen soldiers, do not do work that God and angels don’t like such as putting landmines and setting ambushes. Make peace and live together happily with your family.\r\n','','','2006-12-28 20:56:38','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4836,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-12_1.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 00:51:28','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4837,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-12_1.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','Thank you for your prayers and for your stand with the people of Burma.<br>\r\nGod Bless you,<br>\r\nA Relief Team Leader<br>\r\nFree Burma Rangers','','','2006-12-28 00:56:03','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4944,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images','idx3','member','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-03_1.jpg','','','','','','2006-12-28 19:34:21','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4945,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-03_2.jpg','idx0','page','title','SELF','Families fleeing Toungoo District.','','','','','2006-12-28 20:44:09','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4838,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-12_2.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 00:52:56','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4839,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-12_2.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','It is not easy to trust God with all of our hearts, especially when we suffer. But there is no other way to live with faith than to give God our whole hearts no matter what each of us are facing wherever we are. May we give ourselves wholeheartedly to God as He leads us on.','','','2006-12-28 00:52:56','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4840,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-12_3.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 00:53:36','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4841,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-12_3.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','These pictures of people praying, hiding, fleeing and carrying children to safety show faith, suffering, uncertainty, love in action and hope. In Proverbs 3:5-6, we are urged, “Trust in the LORD with all your heart and lean not on your own understanding; in all your ways acknowledge Him, and He will make your paths straight.”','','','2006-12-28 00:54:07','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4842,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-1_1.jpg','idx1','Page','source','','','','','','','2006-12-28 00:54:40','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(4843,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-01_1.jpg','idx1','Page','description','','','','<b>2006 Offensive by Burma Army Displaces Over 25,000 Villagers in Northern Karen State</b><br>\r\nThe people in these photos are some of the over 25,000 displaced by the Burma Army in the worst offensive since 1997. The unrelenting attacks in the Karen State are part of the plan by the dictators to completely dominate, chase out or crush any Karen people in these areas.','','','2006-12-28 19:47:33','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4946,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images/DOP_2007-03_2.jpg','idx3','member_of','','/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2007/images','','','','','','2006-12-28 19:34:22','2007-10-15 00:34:21',NULL,1,'',''),(4947,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of