l the Shan teams.','','','2013-02-12 17:08:16','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,1,'',''),(8217,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/sai1_400.jpg','idx1','page','source','','','','','','','2013-02-12 17:08:16','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(8218,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/Sha prepares to come across_400.jpg','idx1','page','description','','','','“Sha” was 8 years old and on her way to school when mushrooms caught her eye. \r\nAs she stepped off of the path to pick some, the landmine exploded and her life \r\nwas forever changed. Sha lost her right leg almost to her hip. That was nearly nine \r\nyears ago and she has grown from a little girl to a young woman, unable to run \r\nand play with others.','','','2013-02-12 17:08:56','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,1,'',''),(8219,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/Sha prepares to come across_400.jpg','idx1','page','source','','','','','','','2013-02-12 17:08:56','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,1,'','CCB'),(8220,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/Student at GLC program, identifying Shan State on map of Burma_400.jpg','idx1','page','source','','','','','','','2013-02-12 17:09:20','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,1,'','FBR'),(8221,'/IDX/Prayer/Day_of_Prayer/2013/images/SlideShow/400/Toh Picture_400.jpg','idx1','page','description','','','','I am a medic working with Free Burma Rangers based in the \r\nJungle School of Medicine Kawthoolei (JSM-K). Since I was \r\nsmall, I have been interested in medicine. When teachers \r\nused to ask me, “What do you want to be?” I used to say, “A \r\ndoctor.” During the many years of civil war in Burma, the \r\nKaren people have had poor access to health care. There are \r\nsimply not enough health workers. The few we have do not \r\nhave the chance to study medicine to a very high level. So \r\nmany Karen people die from causes that are simple to treat.  --Toh Win, Medic at JSM-K','','','2013-02-12 17:09:43','0000-00-00 00:00:00